		<div id="comment_body_61506184">A single bitcoin transaction can process around 1,000 transfers. But my limited understanding is the transfers chosen are based on the client crunching the hashes and is generally based on bids. If you don't bid enough, it may be a while before your transfer is processed. At one point in the past, I heard about weeks long delays.</div>
